[Cases continue to surge because of low vaccination rates in many locations, together with the spread of the d variant, which is reportedly 60% more transmissible. In Israel, 70% of cases involve the delta variant, with half of those cases being children, and most concerning, one-third of those cases are vaccinated. This gives further support to the variant being able to escape neutralization from vaccine-induced antibody. - Mod.LK]

