[2] Delta plus variant
Date: Tue 22 Jun 2021 20:16 IST
Source: Hindustan Times [edited]
https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/delta-plus-variant-traced-in-9-countries-uk-us-japan-china-on-list-101624366833126.html


Even as nations rush to vaccinate large chunks of the population as they race against coronavirus, a new variant of the virus called Delta plus has come under the global watch. Even as they kept their guard up against the highly transmissible delta variant, first found in India, at least 9 countries have started reporting cases of the mutated delta plus variant strain. These countries include the United States, the United Kingdom, Portugal, Switzerland, Japan, Poland, Nepal, China, and Russia.

The delta plus variant is also called B.1.617.2.1 or AY.1 strain. Of the details emerging about the delta plus variant, the most noticeable one is the fact that the new strain is resistant to the monoclonal antibodies cocktail.

India on Tuesday [22 Jun 2021] said it has at least 22 cases of the delta plus variant, which the government has classified as a variant of interest so far. The strain from which it has mutated from delta has been listed as a variant of concern by the World Health Organization (WHO).

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[The variant B.1.617.2.1 or AY.1 is characterized by the acquisition of K417N mutation in the spike protein of SARS-CoV-2. While it is being reported that the delta plus variant is resistant to monoclonal antibodies used as a therapeutic, casirivimab and imdevimab, more data from experimental studies are needed to confirm this. Blood from immunized individuals and patients who recovered from infection need to be tested to determine if the antibody is effective at neutralizing the virus. Read more at http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/83538387.cms.]

