<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 22 Jun 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20JUNE22_1624472403.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 37.2% of daily case numbers and 41.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 70.92 million cases. Brazil reported over 44 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Colombia (27 818), Argentina (10 395), while the USA did not report any cases over the last 48 hours; 9 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 14.6% of daily case numbers and 14.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 55.41 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Sweden, Belgium, Switzerland (one case), and Kazakhstan, among others; 3 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 10.8% of daily case numbers and 7.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.72 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (10 485) over the last 24 hours, followed by Oman, Iraq, Afghanistan, Tunisia, UAE, Kuwait, and Saudi Arabia. Pakistan, Egypt, and Jordan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 6.0% of daily case numbers and 3.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.81 million cases. South Africa (9160) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Namibia, Botswana, Zambia, and Uganda. Cameroon, Gabon, Guinea, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.9 % of daily case numbers and 3.8 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.41 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 5400 cases), followed by Malaysia, Mongolia, Japan, Cambodia, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 24.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 26.0% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 34.18 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 42 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (13 668), Bangladesh (4846), Thailand (4059), and Nepal (3703).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 22 Jun 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

